    InventoryManager
    This class is responsible for managing the inventory of medicines, including adding/removing stock, updating stock count and alert levels, displaying inventory, handling replenishment requests, and managing medicine details.
    InventoryService
    The InventoryService class manages inventory-related operations including displaying stock, submitting replenishment requests, viewing pending requests, and clearing all requests.
    MedicalRecord
    Represents a medical record for a patient, containing personal details, medical history, and methods for displaying and updating the record.
    Medicine
    Represents a medicine with details such as its ID, name, stock count, and low stock level alert.
    ReplenishmentRequest
    Represents a replenishment request for a particular medicine, including its status, quantity, and requester details.

    Enum representing different roles in the system.
